Author:
Vol / Page: 3
Edition:
Quote: The Coromadel to Thames service car went over a  bank at Lynch's Hill yesterday, where the drop is said to be 80ft, and overturned four times landing wheels up on the beach. The driver was shaken and one passenger rendered unconscious, whilst another, a well known commercial man, had three ribs broken. A lady passenger had a broken collar bone, a child escaping unhurt and uninjured. They were all removed to the Coromandel Hospital.
