Date: 0/5/2003
Source: NZ Geographic
Author:
Vol / Page: No. 63/85
Edition:
Quote: He told me of an odd New Zealand phenomenon, the service car. A cross between a taxi, bus and freight truck, these big cars plied their trade on country roads gathering together the various threads of rural society. Usually soft-topped, and with low doors for easy access, service cars were common throughout the country in the 1920s and 30s.
